2054.subject: BIO
2054.descrlong: Covers the distinguishing characteristics of the major animal groups (phyla); animal development, physiology, biomechanics, and ecology; and natural history and field identification of many important marine, aquatic, and terrestrial animals of central coastal California. (Offered fall and spring semester.)
